### Description

The Angular web-test-runner integration appears to ignore errors that occur in `afterAll` functions or at moments when no spec is executing. This is basically the same bug as https://github.com/blueprintui/web-test-runner-jasmine/issues/25.


### Minimal Reproduction

I found this via code inspection. I haven't been able to get Angular's web-test-runner integration working at all. The only setup instructions I've found are from the [Angular 17.1 announcement](https://blog.angular-university.io/angular-17-1-release/). They're incomplete, bit-rotted, and look like they might not have worked even when new.

That said, unless there's a second reporter hiding out somewhere in Angular's integration that handles suite-level failures, I'm pretty confident that adding this spec file to a working Angular web-test-runner setup will reproduce the problem:


```
describe('a suite', function() {
	it('a spec', function() {});

	afterAll(function() {
		throw new Error('nope');
	});
});

afterAll(function() {
	throw new Error('nope');
});
```

The output should indicate that both the top suite and the "a suite" suite failed with the corresponding exceptions. Based on reading the code I think that Angular's implementation, like blueprintui/web-test-runner-jasmine, will indicate an overall status of failed without providing any specifics about the failures.

